---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---
<Base
  title="Privacy — Helix"
  description="The Helix website collects nothing about you on its servers: no cookies, no analytics, no tracking, no accounts. The interactive demo saves your own data in your browser, on your device, and sends it nowhere. Stated plainly."
>
  <section class="page-hero dark">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow">privacy · effective 2026-06-10</span>
      <h1>This site collects <em>nothing about you</em>.</h1>
      <p class="lede">No cookies, no analytics, no tracking pixels, no ads, no accounts. The same discipline the project applies to its trust claims applies here: everything that happens when you load a page — and everything the interactive demo stores in your own browser — is listed below, completely.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="wrap">
      <div class="split">
        <div class="split-label">
          <span class="eyebrow">The policy</span>
          <h2>Everything that happens, listed.</h2>
          <p>A static website has a short, finite list of data flows. This is all of them.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="prose">
          <h3>What this site does not do</h3>
          <p>It sets no cookies. It loads no analytics, advertising, or tracking scripts of any kind. It has no user accounts, no comment systems, and no contact forms — contact happens over email or GitHub, on those services&rsquo; own terms. This site has no server-side application and no database; it cannot record anything you do, because there is nowhere for it to record it.</p>

          <h3>Hosting</h3>
          <p>The site is served as static files by <strong>Cloudflare Pages</strong>, and the domain (<code>299bytes.com</code>), DNS, and TLS certificate are also handled by Cloudflare. Like any web host, Cloudflare may keep standard access logs — IP address, user agent, requested URL, timestamp — to operate and secure the service; those logs belong to and are governed by <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/">Cloudflare&rsquo;s own privacy policy</a>. This project does not add to them, enrich them, or use them for tracking. No third-party analytics (including Cloudflare Web Analytics) is enabled.</p>

          <h3>Fonts</h3>
          <p>The marketing pages load the Geist and JetBrains Mono typefaces from the Google Fonts CDN. When your browser fetches those font files it sends Google a standard web request (your IP address and user agent), governed by Google&rsquo;s privacy policy. This is the only resource the site loads from outside Cloudflare. The demo pages under <code>/demo/</code> are dependency-free and load no external fonts or scripts at all.</p>

          <h3>Your demo data stays in your browser</h3>
          <p>The interactive demo can save data using your browser&rsquo;s <strong>local storage</strong> — on your device only. Depending on what you use, that includes: your saved conversations, your prompt library, pinned notes, a custom system prompt, generation settings, and display preferences such as the light/dark theme. None of it is ever transmitted: there is no account and no server to send it to, and this site never reads it back to itself. You can erase all of it at any time with your browser&rsquo;s &ldquo;clear site data&rdquo;, or with the demo&rsquo;s own new-chat and delete controls. Nothing is stored until you actually use those features.</p>

          <h3>Optional voice features</h3>
          <p>If you click the microphone button, the demo uses your browser&rsquo;s built-in speech recognition to transcribe what you say. Depending on your browser, that audio may be sent to your browser&rsquo;s maker (for example, Google for Chrome) and is governed by their policy — it is entirely opt-in, and nothing listens until you click. The read-aloud feature uses your browser&rsquo;s local speech synthesis and sends nothing anywhere.</p>

          <h3>The demo on this site</h3>
          <p>On this public site the demo runs <strong>no backend</strong>. The live chat, deep-think, and inspection features require a local server you would run yourself; on <code>299bytes.com</code> they stay inert, so nothing you type there is processed or transmitted. What you can see here are replays of real, captured runs, committed as self-contained files that execute entirely in your browser from that committed data.</p>

          <h3>External links</h3>
          <p>Links to GitHub, Hugging Face, and other external sites leave this site; their privacy policies apply there.</p>

          <h3>Changes &amp; questions</h3>
          <p>If anything on this list changes, this page changes with it, with a new effective date. Questions: the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="cta dark">
    <div class="wrap">
      <span class="eyebrow">The same rule everywhere</span>
      <h2>Nothing hidden, here either.</h2>
      <p>The project&rsquo;s whole premise is that you shouldn&rsquo;t have to take anyone&rsquo;s word for what software does — including this website.</p>
      <div class="btn-row">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/trust-chain/">See the trust chain <span class="arrow">&rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/contact/">Contact</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
